   <narrative xml:lang="EN">INF</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the last four years members of the KWA have been implementing programs individually. This has been working well and some modest attempts have been made to look for further synergy. This year we see the potential to combine different expertise to contribute towards a similar goal through synergies and complementarities&#x2019; strategies yet there has been lack of integration of members in the programs.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SASOL suppervised sand dam construction and was involved in site selection and confirmation, technical designing and supervision during the construction period. SASOL artisans were brought onboard to build the capacities of the local masons in sand dam construction through hands on learning. Being a new technology to the community, there is call for further strengthening of their technical capacities through guided practice during sand dam construction.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">THROUGH LOW COST TECHNOLOGIES</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project shall include the following key activities:-

1.	Mainstreaming the program through country coordinator, this contract is part of a bigger WASH alliance activity; all activities will be shared with the country coordinator for him to coordinate the different activities. 

2.	 SASOL is the grantee and will coordinate the activities under this grant. The main aim of the grant is to enable local organizations to better understand sand dam implementation.</narrative>
